definitions.definition: Introduces a comparison, and is associated with comparatives , and with words such as more , less , and fewer . Typically, it seeks to measure the force of an adjective or similar description between two predicates .
examples: Patients diagnosed more recently are probably surviving an average of longer than two years.
No player is more skillful than Greg.
